comments.body:
@vrothberg good question, I don't recall discussing having the local linux buildfarm also go through the socket and don't see it on the design doc either, but that may just have been discussed verbally.
I went with the given approach of abi and tunnel following the approach we usually take with the podman commands. 

It does make sense to have everything in tunnel and use the local socket, but given that this PR is currently working, I would like to not block this on making that change. Once this PR is reviewed and merged I can move everything to tunnel, test it out, and open a PR if everything goes well.

@nalind looks like you can't build a manifest list without giving it a name. For the `podman build` command, if we use `--manifest` we have to give it a value even if we don't set anything for `-t`. So the list created here will have a name including an ID. Similarly, with `podman manifest create` you have to give it a name.

For `podman farm build`, I think we should make `-t` a requirement to ensure we have a name to give to the manifest list. We should also hide the `--manifest` flag from farm build.

Update: Fixed to make `--tag` a requirement for far build
